      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(signal): require approval id header for reactions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nHarden Signal approval reaction binding so native reaction targets are only attached to canonical OpenClaw approval prompts.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Require a canonical `ID: <approvalId>` header before Signal extracts approval reaction bindings from outbound text.\n- Require `/approve <approvalId> ...` command lines to match that header before reaction hints or targets are registered.\n- Preserve Signal target-mode exec and plugin approvals by rendering canonical approval IDs before send-time reaction binding runs.\n- Add Signal regression coverage for copied approval-command snippets, mismatched prompt IDs, runtime-built native approval prompts, and send/reaction resolution behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-signal.config.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-native.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts extensions/signal/src/send.approval-reactions.behavior.test.ts --reporter=dot`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/signal/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-native.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-native.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts extensions/signal/src/send.approval-reactions.behavior.test.ts`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\n## Notes\n\nBehavior addressed: Signal approval reactions now bind only to canonical approval prompts with matching IDs.\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on branch `757`, commit `4b7b406edb`, Node `v22.22.2`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-signal.config.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-handler.runtime.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-native.test.ts extensions/signal/src/approval-reactions.test.ts extensions/signal/src/send.approval-reactions.behavior.test.ts --reporter=dot`.\nEvidence after fix: focused Signal approval suite passed with 4 test files and 40 tests.\nObserved result after fix: ordinary outbound snippets without canonical approval IDs do not append reaction hints or register reaction targets; canonical target-mode exec/plugin prompts render `ID: <approvalId>`, keep matching `/approve <approvalId> ...` commands, append native reaction hints at send time, register the returned Signal timestamp as a reaction target, and resolve authorized thumbs-up reactions to the matching approval ID.\nWhat was not tested: delivery through an external Signal service to real devices. The available behavioral proof exercises production OpenClaw Signal renderer, native approval runtime delivery, outbound send, target registration, and reaction resolution code against a deterministic local native Signal JSON-RPC endpoint.\n",
